OL,3,CFirst 'bionic peer' enters House of
OL,4,CLords, vowing to fight for sepsis
OL,5,Csurvivors
OL,7,FLord Mackinlay, of Richborough, is the
OL,8,Ffirst quadruple amputee to be
OL,9,Fintroduced to the House of Lords after
OL,10,Fhe was given a peerage in Rishi
OL,11,FSunak's dissolution honours list.
OL,13,FThe former Conservative MP for South
OL,14,FThanet, was rushed to hospital and put
OL,15,Fin a 16-day induced coma in September
OL,16,F2023. His wife was told he only had a
OL,17,F5% chance of survival.
OL,19,FThe 57-year-old then had both legs and
OL,20,Fboth arms amputated in December.
